      "content": "I see. So you're saying the \"skeptics\" are basically just people with an interest in keeping things unregulated? That's a pretty strong way to frame it. If I'm presenting this to the board, shouldn't I also mention that a lot of people think the whole \"existential risk\" thing is just a way for big companies to create \"regulatory capture\"—basically using fear to build moats that keep smaller startups from competing?",
